Anonymous Sat 13 Mar 2021 05:27:20 No.37043254 Report
Quoted By:
>>37039752
I write in vim & run a spellcheck there. Edit in same after a 2-3 week break. By this point I should have all my editing markups completed/removed.
Import to LibreOffice, because I find talking everything out much easier if formatted it to a hardcover-sized page. If my tongue twists, it's too complicated.

After that it's all checking and judgement calls. I've used hemingway like >>37039770 but find it rarely tells me anything new at that late of a stage. Adverbs are not evil, but a writer should judge them well before final editing. Same for passive voice. At times passive is the most concise and clear way to say something. And if I write a longer sentence, it's for a damned reason. Algorithms don't judge your pacing or paragraphs. Anything that survives drunken writing, sober editing, and a spoken readthrough - it is good to reconsider those. But I rarely change my mind wholesale.
